DISCLAIMER:

This project is intended for EDUCATIONAL AND PORTFOLIO PURPOSES ONLY.

All hardening scripts in this repository are designed for isolated lab
environments running Ubuntu 24.04 LTS. These scripts MUST NOT be applied
to production systems without:

  1. Change management approval from the system owner and security team
  2. Application compatibility testing for all running workloads
  3. A tested rollback plan (VM snapshot + backup files)
  4. A scheduled maintenance window with monitoring in place
  5. Post-change validation and monitoring

Hardening controls — particularly sysctl network parameters and mount
options — can affect application behavior, network routing, and system
functionality. Always test in an isolated environment first.

The author accepts no liability for system outages, data loss, or
service disruptions resulting from the use of these scripts outside
of the intended lab context.

All sample data uses dummy hostnames (ubuntu-lab-01), dummy IP addresses
(10.0.0.30), and fictional SCA scores. No real organizational configuration
data is included in this repository.
